OL,3,CKing's Christmas message to reflect on
OL,4,Chis and Kate's cancer
OL,6,FThe King wanted this year's message to
OL,7,Freflect on the challenging year he has
OL,8,Fsuffered following his cancer
OL,9,Fdiagnosis for which he is still
OL,10,Freceiving treatment.
OL,12,FThe location also means the King has
OL,13,Fincluded the Princess of Wales in his
OL,14,Fthoughts after she had her own cancer
OL,15,Fdiagnosis followed by a course of
OL,16,Fchemotherapy.
OL,18,FThe year-end speech, always broadcast
OL,19,Fat 3pm on Christmas Day, is Charles'
OL,20,Fthird since he ascended to the throne.
